<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia Backs Syria, Lebanon over Israeli </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia has expressed
its firm support for Syria and Lebanon in their demand that Israel
withdraw from south Lebanon unconditionally, the Saudi Press
Agency reported on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The kingdom expressed hope that the prospect of carrying out
the United Nations Resolution 425 by Israel will be coupled with a
revival of the peace talks between Syria and Israel from the point
they have reached, a statement issued by the Saudi government late
Friday night said.
</P>
<P>
Israel approved the adoption of the U.N. resolution on April 1,
paving the way for its withdrawal from south Lebanon. But,
meanwhile, it demanded that the Lebanese government agree to
security arrangements for the bordering areas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Syria, which agree to coordinate their stances on
key issues, have rejected Israel's offer, maintaining that the
Jewish state should withdraw from south Lebanon unconditionally
under the U.N. resolution.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. Resolution 425 passed in 1978 after Israeli invasion
of Lebanon calls for an unconditional Israeli pullback from
south Lebanon, where it set up a security zone in 1985 to
allegedly protect its northern areas from cross-border attacks by
Muslim guerrillas.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Prime Minister Rafik Hariri visited the Saudi Arabia
last month and discussed with Saudi Crown Prince Abdullah Ibn
Abdul-Aziz Israel's attempt to dodge the implementation of the
U.N. resolution. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
