<HEADLINE> Ethiopian Population Stands at 58,652,158 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The central statistical
authority of Ethiopia announces on Saturday that the total number
of the Ethiopian population at present stands at 58,652,158.
</P>
<P>
According to an official statistical report issued by the
authority, 50,149,190 of the population are living in rural areas
while the balance 8,502,968 are urban dwellers.
</P>
<P>
With regard to gender, the report indicates that 29,502,297
people are male while the remaining 29,149,861 are female.
</P>
<P>
The reports says the capital, Addis Ababa is home to 2,432,426
people and the Oromia national state is the most populated region
with 20,507,101 people.
</P>
<P>
The authority estimates that with a growth rate of about three
percent annually, the country's population will be 61,654,146 in
2000 and will reach 94,246,000 in 2010.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia has the third largest population in Africa after
Nigeria and Egypt. 
</P>
</TEXT>
