<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rwanda Kicks off Anti-Famine Campaign </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- The Rwandan government has
launched a campaign of sensitization of the population to fight
famine looming in many parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Government top officials have started touring the country
since Wednesday, visiting agricultural projects, and
co-operatives of farmers in a bid to encourage them to increase
productivity.
</P>
<P>
Areas, like the southern and western parts of the country are
badly hit by famine and the local population is appealing for
food relief.
</P>
<P>
In Gikongoro prefecture, south of the capital, the situation
is dramatic, as indicated by its Prefect Augustin Mutijima
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Since last November, 400 people died of hunger or
nutrition-related diseases, " he pointed out, blaming the
pandemonium on the acid soils of his region, and the low
purchasing power of farmers who can not afford fertilizers.
</P>
<P>
"We have been sending missions in that area to assess the
situation, "an official of the World Food Program (WFP) told
Rwanda News Agency, adding that the agency has been operational
in south Rwanda where it has supported agricultural projects
through the "food for work " system.
</P>
<P>
WFP is also involved in providing food assistance to
vulnerable groups in 285 nutritional centers of the area, the
official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
