<HEADLINE> Drought Grips Western Guangdong Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The prolonged drought gripping
western Guangdong Province has severely affected the maturation of
early Spring rice in the cities of Maoming and Zhanjiang.
</P>
<P>
The cities, both of which are major grain production
bases, have suffered from a severe shortage of precipitation over
the past three months.
</P>
<P>
The average rainfall for Maoming between January and March 1998
dropped by some 33 percent on last year's same period, with the
figure for Zhanjiang falling by close to 30 percent.
</P>
<P>
The two cities have responded to the problem by purchasing
irrigation equipment, and over 700,000 Maoming farmers are
currently watering their fields on a daily basis.
</P>
<P>
Reports that related efforts have greatly relieved related
problems in various areas.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
