<HEADLINE> Canadian Firm Interested in Invest in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Canada's official export credit
agency, the Export Development Corporation (EDC), has put forward
proposals to finance a number of projects in Bangladesh, the
national news agency BSS reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The EDC had approached Bangladesh's public sector with at least
five proposals to finance projects in power, railway, pulp and
paper, telecommunications and aviation, and it also proposed to
finance projects of two private telecom companies, a senior EDC
official told the BSS.
</P>
<P>
Anis Karim, the EDC's regional manager of Asia and the Pacific,
said he was waiting for a positive reply from the Bangladeshi
government and the private sector which were studying the
proposals.
</P>
<P>
The EDC's short-term financing to some insurance companies on
Canadian exports to Bangladesh was close to 100 million U.S.
dollars, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of many Canadian companies had visited
Bangladesh with initiatives of the EDC, showing that they were
eager to invest in Bangladesh, he added. 
</P>
