<HEADLINE> Sino-Japanese Pharmaceutical Joint Venture Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, April 12 (Xinhua) -- NCPC Beta Co. Ltd., a
Sino-Japanese pharmaceutical joint venture which produces
semi-synthetic antibiotics, recently entered operations in
Shijiazhuang, capital of north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
NCPC Beta was established by Nichimen Corporation of Japan and
Shijiazhuang-based North China Pharmaceutical Corporation (NCPC),
China's largest antibiotics manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
Nichimen provided 20.4 million US dollars, or 34 percent of the
total investment, with the figure representing company's largest
investment in China to date.
</P>
<P>
The new export-oriented company is expected to become one of
China's major producers of semi-synthetic antibiotics. 
</P>
