<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading U.S. Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading U.S. newspapers Sunday:
</P>
<P>
The New York Times:
</P>
<P>
-- Two years from the start of the 2000 Census, it is shaping
up as the most contentious in 80 years, generating a firestorm of
debate and strategizing in Congress and litigation aimed at
blocking the Census Bureau from changing the way it does business.
</P>
<P>
-- George J. Mitchell, the American negotiator in the Irish
