<HEADLINE> WEU Police Advisers Team to Stay One More Year in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The Western European Union (WEU)
has decided to extend one more year for its police advisers team
which it sent to Albania last year.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian Interior Ministry received a note from the WEU
Saturday saying that the police advisors team will stay in Albania
till April 12, 1999, Albanian newspaper "The Voice of People"
quoted a spokesman from the ministry as saying on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The WEU will decide whether to extend the stay of the police
advisers team further or not in October, the spokesman also said.
</P>
<P>
The police advisers team was sent to Albania last May at the
request of the Albanian government to help Albania reorganize
police force and restore order.
</P>
<P>
There are now 60 police officers from 20 European countries
working in the advisers team. 
