<HEADLINE> Thai Airways Plane Leaves Runway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, April 12 (Xinhua) -- A MD-11 passenger aircraft
operated by Thai Airways International Ltd. veered off the runway
at the Shanghai Hongqiao International Airport this afternoon. No
injuries were reported.
</P>
<P>
Flight T-G664 from Bangkok to Shanghai landed at approximately
16:00 today and came to a halt some 30 meters off the runway.
</P>
<P>
The aircraft landed in heavy rain, with the 800-meter confirmed
visibility at the time conforming with landing requirements.
</P>
<P>
Hongqiao Airport General Manager Li Derun rushed to the scene
for direct rescue efforts, with more than 200 members of the armed
police arriving soon thereafter to evacuate passengers.
</P>
<P>
Some 10-odd emergency fire-fighting vehicles and ambulances
sped to the scene to render assistance.
</P>
<P>
The airport closed temporarily, and airport sources noted that
the incident will affect more than 100 flights scheduled for
today.  
