<HEADLINE> Iran's Top Leaders Meet Over Mayor's Detention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Iran's top leaders met Saturday
evening to discuss the detention of Tehran Mayor Gholamhussein
Karbaschi on charge of embezzlement, an Iranian conservative
newspaper reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The English-language daily Tehran Times quoted a reliable
source as saying that President Mohammad Khatami, Parliament
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri, Chief Justice Ayatollah Mohammad
Yazdi, Chairman of the State Expediency Council and former
president Hashemi Rafsanjani reviewed the Karbaschi case on late
Saturday evening.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on condition of anonymity, the source said that
the leaders reached "some sort of conclusion" on Karbaschi's
detention, but adding that "it's not the right time to
reveal exactly what they have decided."
</P>
<P>
He said that the results of their discussion would be delivered
to Iranian supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, who summoned
them on Wednesday, asking them to review the case in order to
quell a growing power struggle in the country.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted another source as ruling out the possibility
that Karbaschi would be freed from prison.
</P>
<P>
Karbaschi was detained on April 4 for a huge financial scandal,
which was rejected by Karbaschi himself. Pro-Khatami factions
termed it political revenge against the mayor for his support
for Khatami in the presidential elections last May.
</P>
<P>
Enjoying Karbaschi's desperate support in the presidential
elections, Khatami won a landslide victory over Nateq-Nouri, a
conservative leader, who won support from Yazdi.
</P>
<P>
However, Gholamhussein Mohseni, chief of the special judicial
bench in charge of investigating violations of civil employees,
rejected the allegations that Karbaschi's case was politically
motivated, saying that "we do not seek political goals but
deliver justice."
</P>
<P>
He added that Karbaschi was detained according to legal
procedure and would be tried openly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
