<HEADLINE> Over 90 Tanzanian Miners Buried by Landslide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, April 12 (Xinhua) -- More than 90 miners have
been buried by landslide in a tanzanite mine in Arusha in north
Tanzania following a downpour on Thursday night, Dar es Salaam
newspapers reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The miners are feared dead as they have gone 300 meters deep
in the pits and the whole mining area is flooded after prolonged
rainfall, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Arusha Regional Commissioner Daniel ole Njoolay confirmed
the news Sunday, saying that rescue operation has been difficult
due to lack of equipment and poor road conditions damaged by
floods.
</P>
<P>
"Nothing can be done..." Njoolay told Xinhua in a telephone
interview, adding that water pumps, bulldozers and other rescue
equipment to excavate soil are urgently needed.
</P>
<P>
He also said the mining area in Merelani, some 40 kilometers
away from the Arusha town, is difficult to reach because roads
leading to it have been washed away by floods.
</P>
<P>
"It's still raining," he said.
</P>
<P>
The regional commissioner said that he has formed a rescue
team consisting of government officials, police and fire brigades
and sanitation departments, and mobilized people with tractors to
reach the site.  
</P>
</TEXT>
