<HEADLINE> Death Toll in Iran's Earthquake Reaches 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, April 12 (Xinhua) -- The death toll of the
earthquake in eastern Iran has reached 12 and the injured
over 30, Tehran radio reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Quake, measuring at 5.9 degree on the open-ended Richter
scale, hit Birjand region of Iran's northeastern province of
Khorasan. Some 20 aftershocks with magnitude ranging from 2.6 to
4.8 degrees jolted the region.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that 10 people were killed by the
quake, which inflicted damages on 24 villages and 581 residential
units.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another earthquake at 4.1 degree hit the city of
Khalkhal in the northwestern province of Ardebil at 00:55
hours local time Sunday, the Iranian official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
The seismological base of geophysics institute of Tehran
University registered the epicenter of the tremor in the vicinity
of Khalkhal, 350 kilometers northwest of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
No report has yet been received on possible damages inflicted
by the quake.
</P>
<P>
Last month, a strong earthquake at 6.8 degree rocked Iran's
central province of Kerman, killing five people and injuring 50
others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
