<HEADLINE> 13 Zimbabweans Killed, 158 Injured in Three </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, April 12 (Xinhua) -- Thirteen Zimbabweans were killed
and 158 others injured in road accidents since the beginning of
the Easter holiday on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
In the same period last year, there were eight deaths and 30
injuries in road accidents, the Sunday Mail reported.
</P>
<P>
Police Press and Public Relations Officer Joe Manyakaidze said
that most of the accidents were due to speeding, lack of
attention on the part of the drivers and defective vehicles which
were being used to ferry people from different areas.
</P>
<P>
The paper quoted Manyakaidze as saying that about 101 vehicles
had so far been impounded and 20 tickets issued for drunken
driving.
</P>
<P>
Although this year's figures were higher than that of last
year, the staff officer for the National Highway Patrol, Chief
Superintendent Martin Simbi said, this year's Good Friday was one
of the safest due to a heavy police presence on the roads,
favorable weather and a changing attitude in a growing number of
drivers toward reckless driving.
</P>
<P>
Simbi urged those who are traveling to remain cautious on the
roads as they make their way back at the end of the holiday
tomorrow. 
</P>
