<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italian FM Hails Northern Ireland Peace Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini Saturday expressed "sincere joy" over a historic agreement
aimed at ending the three-decade-old strife in Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
In a message to his British and Irish counterparts Robin Cook
and David Andrews, Dini praised "the courage, spirit of compromise
and far-sightedness" demonstrated by government and political
leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The agreement contains a message of hope for all those in
Europe and elsewhere in the world engaged in equally-entrenched
conflicts, Dini said.
</P>
<P>
The long-awaited peace deal resolving three-decade-long
conflict over British rule of Northern Ireland was finally struck
on Friday by the political parties involved in the peace talks.
</P>
</TEXT>
