<HEADLINE> Samaranch Plans To Visit Cuba This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAVANA, April 11 (Xinhua) -- International Olympic Committee
president Juan Antonio Samaranch said he will visit Cuba this
year, according to local reports here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The IOC president reiterated in a statement quoted by local
paper Granma that "I will do my best to go to Havana this year, to
meet all the people who direct sports, and as I usually do when I
travel to the island, to meet with Fidel Castro."
</P>
<P>
Samaranch, Spanish ambassador in the Soviet Union and in
Mongolia before becoming in 1980 the leader of the Olympic
organization, expressed his satisfaction for the recent Madrid
government decision to appoint an ambassador to Cuba.
</P>
<P>
Samaranch expressed in a statement made in Lausanne,
Switzerland, his confidence that Cuban sports will maintain its
high level. 
</P>
