<HEADLINE> Tillstrom Enters Finals of Indian Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Defending champion and fifth
seed Mikael Tillstrom of Sweden spent just 62 minutes to dismiss
second-seeded Australian Todd Woodbridge 6-2, 6-2 in the
semi-finals of the Indian Open on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Tillstrom's opponent in Sunday's final will be top-seeded
Australian Patrick Rafter, who fought hard to beat unseeded Indian
Leander Paes 6-3, 7-6(7-5).
</P>
