The Swede broke Woodbridge's serve in the first game of both
sets and never gave the Australian a chance to get into the match.
</P>
<P>
However, U.S. Open champion Rafter was taken to a second set
tie-break to beat off the Indian challenge which lasted 95 minutes
throughout the match. 
