<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, April 12 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- A total of 5,584 Iraqi prisoners of war released by
Iran have come back home, Iraqi Foreign Under-Secretary Riyadh
al-Qaisi said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
In a television interview, al-Qaisi said that in a new round of
repatriation of POWs early this month, Iran freed 5,592 Iraqis, of
whom one died of heart attack during the process and seven others
refused to return home.
</P>
<P>
During the biggest POW swap between the two countries since
1990, Iraq also freed three Iranian POWs and 316 others it
classified as civil law detainees. (Iraq-Iran-POWs)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA -- The governments of Ethiopia and Democratic
Republic of Congo signed here on Saturday a general agreement
which will serve as a basis for the framework of cooperation
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
According to a joint communique issued here at the end of the
five-day state visit to Ethiopia by Democratic Congolese President
Laurent Desire Kabila, the agreement was signed by Kabila and
Ethiopian President Negasso Gidada at a ceremony held at the
National Palace here. (Ethiopia-agreement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LONDON -- David Trimble, leader of Ulster Unionis Part (UUP),
won a vote of confidence over the Northern Ireland peace agreement
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Some 78 members of the UUP's 110-strong policy-making executive
voted for the deal by a majority of two to one, according to
officials emerging from a UUP meeting in Belfast.
</P>
<P>
The peace deal now faces approval by a meeting of the party's
council on April 17. (UK-UPP-Peace Agreement) 
</P>
