<DATE_TIME> 1998-04-12 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Hails Northern Ireland Peace Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, April 11 (Xinhua) -- Egypt expressed welcome on Saturday
to a peace agreement on resolving conflicts in Northern Ireland
and voiced hope that it could serve as a model for making peace in
the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa told reporters that his
country is satisfied with the understanding reached by all the
parties involved in the Northern Ireland peace talks.
</P>
<P>
A peace agreement was signed on Friday by the British and Irish
governments and eight political parties concerned with the future
of Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
Negotiations with goodwill and keenness to make peace have
actually led to this result, Moussa said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that any other parties can follow suit to achieve
the same positive results and that any other problems can be
solved in the same way.
</P>
<P>
"The Middle East peace talks are lacking this good will,
particularly vis-a-vis the Israeli stance on withdrawal from the
occupied Palestinian and Arab territories according to the
international resolutions," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
